{"id":"project-LICHEN-g4il","title":"oscore_ctx_persist_ssn passes eui64 pointer after mutex release","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/oscore/oscore.c
Lines: 882-916

The oscore_ctx_persist_ssn function saves a pointer to peer_eui64 while holding the mutex, then releases the mutex and calls the write callback with that pointer:

```c
k_mutex_lock(&s_ctx_mutex, K_FOREVER);

write_cb = s_nvm_write_cb;
ssn = ctx->sender_seq;
if (ctx->has_peer_eui64) {
    eui64 = ctx->peer_eui64;  // Pointer to internal data
}

k_mutex_unlock(&s_ctx_mutex);  // Mutex released

// ...

ret = write_cb(eui64, ssn);  // Called with pointer to unlocked data
```

If another thread calls oscore_ctx_free() on the context between mutex release and write_cb call, the eui64 pointer becomes dangling. The callback would access freed/wiped memory.

Fix: Copy the eui64 data to a local variable while holding the mutex:
```c
uint8_t eui64_copy[OSCORE_EUI64_LEN];
const uint8_t *eui64 = NULL;

k_mutex_lock(&s_ctx_mutex, K_FOREVER);
if (ctx->has_peer_eui64) {
    memcpy(eui64_copy, ctx->peer_eui64, OSCORE_EUI64_LEN);
    eui64 = eui64_copy;
}
ssn = ctx->sender_seq;
write_cb = s_nvm_write_cb;
k_mutex_unlock(&s_ctx_mutex);
```

